[3.3.1 Error identification (Level A)](https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG21/quickref/#error-identification)&nbsp;: If an input error is automatically detected, the item that is in error is identified and the error is described to the user in text.

[3.3.3 Error Suggestion (Level AA)](https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG21/quickref/#error-suggestion)&nbsp;: If an input error is automatically detected and suggestions for correction are known, then the suggestions are provided to the user, unless it would jeopardize the security or purpose of the content.
